Which are valid ways to compute P(A ∪ B)? Select all that apply.


<div class='webex-checkboxgroup' id='webex-96af1774b13a1eb488e9fea7c9100de3' data-answer='YgZNVx0GGwU/'><label><input type='checkbox' autocomplete='off' name='96af1774b13a1eb488e9fea7c9100de3'></input><span>P(A P(B)</span></label><label><input type='checkbox' autocomplete='off' name='96af1774b13a1eb488e9fea7c9100de3'></input><span>P(A) + P(B) − P(A ∩ B)</span></label><label><input type='checkbox' autocomplete='off' name='96af1774b13a1eb488e9fea7c9100de3'></input><span>1 − P((A ∪ B)ᶜ)</span></label><label><input type='checkbox' autocomplete='off' name='96af1774b13a1eb488e9fea7c9100de3'></input><span>P(A) + P(B) if A and B are mutually exclusive</span></label></div>


:::
::: {.webex-solution}

General addition rule subtracts overlap. If disjoint, overlap is 0 so it simplifies. You can also use the complement of the union. The product rule is for intersections under independence, not unions.

